sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K094102
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part uses BBa_J61003 as a backbone and cheZ as the inserted gene. cheZ protein is responsible for the dephosphorylation of cheY protein in bacteria flagella movement. The cheZ operon lacks a terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Li Xinran

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Plasmid for assembly of open reading frame basic parts. A Tet promoter (r0040) and strong ribosome binding site (b0034) lie between the EcoRI and XbaI sites. Insertion of an open reading frame basic part into the XbaI and PstI sites results in constitutive expression but retains basic part utilityin standard assembly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K094100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains the cheZ operon coding region without an rbs nor a terminator. cheZ protein is responsible for the dephosphorylation of cheY protein in bacteria flagella movement.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Liu Chenli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The origin of the cheZ gene comes from E. Coli strain MG1655 chromosome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is without promoter, rbs or terminator.
